International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: 19 March 2012
Source: OIE, WAHID [edited] 25(12)
http://web.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=11776

Brucellosis (Brucella abortus), Belgium
Information received on 19/03/2012 from Dr. Pierre Naassens, Directeur
Santé des Animaux et Sécurité des Produits animaux/ CVO, Direction
Santé des Animaux et Sécurité des Produits animaux, Agence Fédérale
pour la Sécurité de la Chaîne Alimentaire, Bruxelles, Belgium

Summary
Report type Immediate notification
Start date 23/02/2012
Date of first confirmation of the event 02/03/2012
Report date 19/03/2012
Date submitted to OIE 19/03/2012
Reason for notification Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence 31/01/2011
Manifestation of disease Clinical disease
Causal agent Brucella abortus
Nature of diagnosis Suspicion, Clinical, Laboratory (basic),
Laboratory (advanced), Necropsy
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1 Franc-Waret, NAMUR
Date of start of the outbreak 23/02/2012
Outbreak status Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit Farm
Affected animals
Species Cattle
Susceptible 262
Cases 2
Deaths 0
Destroyed 0
Slaughtered 262

Affected Population Beef cattle farm.
Summary of outbreaks Total outbreaks: 1

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection. - Unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments Epidemiological investigation on-going.
It is Brucella abortus Biovar 3.

Control measures
Measures applied
Stamping out
Screening
Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s)
Vaccination prohibited
No treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied
No other measures

Laboratory name and type Veterinary and Agrochemical Research Centre
(CODA - CERVA) (National laboratory)
Tests and results

Species Cattle
Test antibody detection ELISA
Test date 02/03/2012
Result Positive

Species Cattle
Test pathogenic agent isolation on culture
Test date 07/03/2012
Result Positive
Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.
