Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[There were 2 cases of B. abortus on a farm with 104 cattle in November of 2010 but there were no cases in 2011 and this is the first incidence this year. It will be interesting to find the source, if it can be known.

Location of Namur in Walloon region in Belgium on
ProMEDmail/Healthmap is available at: : http://healthmap.org/r/1BIG
